rComments: Beneficial concept of 3 midterms and 1 final with your lowest midterm mark dropped. Difficult multiple choice, heavily based on statistics and is very tricky. Prof reads off the slides which is word for word taken from textbook, so class is helpful in the sense of soaking content in your brain. Definitely read the chapters and use Nelson quizzes!

She's nice and her teaching style and course outline is simple and very straightforward. There are 3 midterms and 1 final, the lowest midterm gets dropped and if you are happy with your mark on the first 2, you don't have to show up to the last one but the final is mandatory. All readings & lectures are fair game for the exams; all exams - 100 MC.

She was very engaging at the beginning of the semester with polls then ended up reading off the powerpoint... there's no point in attending class, just memorize the textbook and you'll ace this course. 3 midterms but one mark is dropped. Her MC are tricky and heavily based on stats
Very nice prof. Lectures reflect the textbook so only really need to do your readings to pass. 3 midterms and takes the best 2 marks.
